# <span id="index"></span>IBIS settings

IBIS settings are used to configure settings like:

-   [General settings](#generalsettings)
-   [Asset management](#assetmanagement)
-   [Data cleanup](#datacleanup)
-   [Identity](#identity)
-   [Managers](#managers)
-   [Employee registrations](#employeeregistrations)
-   [Profile page](#profilepage)
-   [Organization management](#organizationmanagement)
-   [Access](#access)
-   [TreeManager](#treemanager)
-   [Search](#search)

IBIS settings can be managed on the ~/Setting page (or by clicking 'IBIS
settings' in the 'All pages' sidepanel). Click on a card to open up an
sidepanel. Change the setting and click the **Save and close** button
save the changes

<img
src="data:image/png;base64,"
class="figure-img img-fluid rounded border" />
<figcaption>Click a card to open the settings of that card.</figcaption>
</figure>
